Note that $\triangle PAB \sim \triangle PBC$ by the AA Similarity. The ratio of similitude is $\frac{PA}{PB} = \frac{PB}{PC} = \frac{AB}{BC},$ or $$\frac{10}{PB} = \frac{PB}{\sqrt{x^2-100}} = \frac{x}{x\sqrt2} = \frac{1}{\sqrt2}.$$
From $\frac{10}{PB} = \frac{1}{\sqrt2},$ we get $PB=10\sqrt2.$ It follows that from $\frac{10}{PB} = \frac{PB}{\sqrt{x^2-100}},$ we get $x^2=500.$

Finally, the area of $\triangle ABC$ is $$\frac12\cdot AB\cdot AC = \frac12\cdot x^2 = \boxed{250}.$$

